  "details": "GLib provides the core application building blocks for libraries and applications written in C. It provides the core object system used in GNOME, the main loop implementation, and a large set of utility functions for strings and common data structures.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * glib: Integer overflow in in g_escape_uri_string() (CVE-2025-13601)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
